metadata.name: I Can't Fix It #1/25
metadata.description:
“I Can’t Fix It” by WYMN  |  April 21, 2022

Currently unreleased, "I Can't Fix It" is the second single off the debut WYMN EP: Water, Water, Everywhere

"I Can't Fix It" is a compassionate exploration of the realities of loving someone who struggles with addiction. The song’s swelling guitars and intimate, soaring vocals lead listeners on a cinematic journey towards a dramatic release. The meaning of the lyrics evolve alongside its soundscape with the phrase ‘I can’t fix it’ transforming from an expression of melancholic regret to a declaration of personal power. 

WYMN is the artist project of music producer Blaire Michael. The artist name is a combination of three words: whim, women, and hymn. Blaire began making music on a whim during graduate school and writes songs that explore her relationships with the women in her life, as well as her struggles to reconcile her religious upbringing - the hymns of her youth - with her life experiences. The sound of WYMN is hazy, alternative dream rock.

One edition carries a special utility - some call it a 'golden egg'. The number of this edition will be announced after collection.
